Class MainController

  • java.lang.Object
    • application.MainController
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    javafx.fxml.Initializable

    public class MainController
extends java.lang.Object
implements javafx.fxml.Initializable
    This class is the controller of the home screens after login screen: AdmiIn.fxml and StaffIn.fxml for manager and staff respectively, give access to all functions of the app.
    Since:
    2016-12-16
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Mingxuan Mei

      • newOrder1

        public void newOrder1(javafx.event.ActionEvent e)
               throws java.sql.SQLException
        newOrder1 This method provides the "click table once for new order, click again for modify order" function for table 1. The newOrder and historyOrder(Latest Order) pages are overlapping in a StackPane and are send to front when needed. Before the newOrder page is sent to front, the TableView menuTable is populated with current menu with several editable TableColumn. Before the historyOrder page is sent to front, the TableView currentTable is populated with the latest order and not-ordered items in the menu .
        Parameters:
        e - Listener of the Table1 button.
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException
        Since:
        2016-12-16
